stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> IDLE

    IDLE --> HASH_LOCKED: getPage acquires pageHashLock
    HASH_LOCKED --> HIT_FRAME: frame exists
    HASH_LOCKED --> LOADING_OWNER: miss registers PageLoadFuture
    HASH_LOCKED --> WAIT_LOADING: loading exists, release hash/list locks

    HIT_FRAME --> PAGE_LATCHING: release hash/list locks
    LOADING_OWNER --> FILE_IO: reserve frame and set ioState READ
    FILE_IO --> PUBLISH_FRAME: read ok
    FILE_IO --> IO_ERROR: read failed
    PUBLISH_FRAME --> PAGE_LATCHING: clear ioState and wake waiters

    WAIT_LOADING --> RECHECK_FRAME: PageLoadFuture completed
    RECHECK_FRAME --> PAGE_LATCHING: validate page id and space version
    RECHECK_FRAME --> IO_ERROR: future failed

    PAGE_LATCHING --> PAGE_LATCHED: acquire requested S/X latch
    PAGE_LATCHED --> MTR_MEMO: register latch and buffer fix
    MTR_MEMO --> RELEASED: MTR LIFO release

    IDLE --> FLUSH_FIXED: page cleaner fixes dirty frame
    FLUSH_FIXED --> FLUSH_SNAPSHOT: capture page image or pageLSN
    FLUSH_SNAPSHOT --> PAGESTORE_IO: release LRU/flush list locks
    PAGESTORE_IO --> FLUSH_DONE: write through PageStore
    FLUSH_DONE --> RELEASED: unfix or keep dirty if modified again

    IO_ERROR --> ERROR_BROADCAST: remove placeholder
    ERROR_BROADCAST --> RELEASED: wake waiters with exception
    RELEASED --> IDLE
    IDLE --> [*]

    note right of WAIT_LOADING
        Waiters hold only PageLoadFuture wait slot.
        They do not hold Buffer Pool list/hash locks.
    end note

    note right of PAGE_LATCHED
        Page latch protects page body only.
        Row-lock wait must release page latch and buffer fix first.
    end note

